{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["iwl_dev_info_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug report indicates missing PCI subdevice entries for device ID 0x2526 (Intel Wireless-AC 9260) with subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C (the report writes 0x04010 which is 0x4010). In drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c, the iwl_dev_info_table (starting at line 978) contains IWL_DEV_INFO entries for 0x2526 with various subdevice IDs (0x0010, 0x0014, 0x0018, 0x001C, 0x6010, 0x6014, 0x8010, 0x8014, 0xA014, 0xE010, 0xE014), but entries for 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C are absent. These missing entries cause the firmware not to be loaded for cards with those subdevice IDs, since the driver falls through to the generic iwl9000_trans_cfg fallback in iwl_hw_card_ids instead of using the correct iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg configuration with the iwl9260_160_name."
}

